						<summary>

						<p>Same Wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Veṅkaṭapatirāya of Āṉaigondi: Bahudhānya, Tai 3 = 1578 A.D., December 31 (Wednesday).</hi></p>						

						<p>It records a gift of 100 <hi rend="italic">kuḻi</hi> of land in Tiṟibhuvaṉamādēvi-viḷāgam in Kūvam, as <hi rend="italic">guru-pāpattu</hi> (homage to the <hi rend="italic">guru</hi>) to Śālai Appar of Elumaṭṭi by a certain Ṉāraṇappanāyakar. The gift is stated to be for the merit of the <hi rend="italic">ūravar.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
